ns are detailed (60 reagent positions, 75 sample positions, 80 cuvettes, 6mm optical path) and align with high-capacity clinical chemistry analyzers. No conflicts detected between sources. Brand is Merilyzer (Meril Life Sciences), product family is AutoQuant 400 series, specific model is Supremus. This is clearly a diagnostic instrument, not an implant or consumable. Classification as 'Biochemistry Analyzer' under 'Diagnostics' division is accurate. Material specification (stainless steel and polymer) reflects instrument construction. No anatomical scope applies to diagnostic instruments.","proposed_recommended_action":"keep_as_is","proposed_semantic_anatomy_scope":[],"proposed_semantic_brand_system":"Merilyzer AutoQuant","proposed_semantic_coating_default":null,"proposed_semantic_confidence":0.92,"proposed_semantic_family_group":"AutoQuant 400 Series","proposed_semantic_implant_class":"N/A - Diagnostic Instrument","proposed_semantic_material_default":"Stainless Steel and Polymer","proposed_semantic_parent_brand":"Merilyzer","proposed_semantic_procedure_scope":["Clinical Chemistry Testing","Biochemical Analysis","In Vitro Diagnostics"],"proposed_semantic_review_required":false,"proposed_semantic_system_type":"Fully Automatic Biochemistry Analyzer","proposed_semantic_use_case_tags":["High-throughput clinical chemistry","Large laboratory testing","Automated biochemistry","ISE-capable analyzer","Multi-panel testing"],"proposed_web_verification_status":"externally_verified","semantic_anatomy_scope":[],"semantic_brand_system":"Merilyzer AutoQuant","semantic_coating_default":null,"semantic_confidence":0.92,"semantic_conflict_codes":[],"semantic_enriched_at":"2026-03-28T09:39:03.465317+00:00","semantic_implant_class":"N/A - Diagnostic Instrument","semantic_material_default":"Stainless Steel and Polymer","semantic_parent_brand":"Merilyzer","semantic_review_required":false,"semantic_rule_hits":["WEB_FALLBACK_EXTERNALLY_VERIFIED"],"semantic_system_type":"Fully Automatic Bioch